<title type="html"><![CDATA[Using a software emulator's 6502 CPU model]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7467&amp;p=73737#p73737"><![CDATA[
Does anyone here know of a past/present project that utilized any particular software emulator's 6502 model for another purpose (i.e. other than an nes emulator)?  In other words, someone that chopped out, say, Nestopia's C++ 6502 model and used it for something else?<br /><br />I realize the question is a bit strange, but I had an idea for using a software emulator's 6502 model to verify my own emulator's hardware model.  Unfortunately, there are almost 0 comments in the nestopia code and it's hard to figure out exactly what specific files/classes I would need to just use the 6502 model alone and then write a kind of "wrapper" to interface to it and run some code on it.  Then I could look at the software 6502's result and compare it to my hardware 6502's result.<br /><br />Any insight or recommendations would be appreciated.<br /><br />Thanks!<br /><br />Jonathon<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3962">jwdonal</a> — Wed Feb 09, 2011 6:14 pm</p><hr />
